processInput

public void processInput(java.lang.String theFile)
Processes the file containing the input string(s), one per line. BONUS! If the line ends in #f (for fail) or #a (for accept), it denotes whether the machine is supposed to handle the given string. For example, if the line is "aabbcc#a", it means the machine should be able to accept the string "aabbcc". Likewise, "aabc#f" means the machine should fail to accept the string "aabc."

Parameters:
theInput - the filename containing the input strings
